4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING A STATE PROGRAM TO PROVIDE
5 REPLACEMENT FUNDING FOR SCHOOL DISTRICTS THAT ELIMINATE REDUCED-PRICE COPAYMENTS
6 FOR SCHOOL LUNCH AND BREAKFAST; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; PROVIDING AN
7 APPROPRIATION; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Program to eliminate reduced-price copayments for school lunch
12 and breakfast -- legislative intent -- rulemaking. (1) The legislature intends to strengthen the opportunity of
13 each child to develop the child's full education potential in accordance with the goal of the people articulated in
14 Article X, section 1(1), of the Montana constitution. The legislature recognizes that:
15 (a) adequate and proper nutrition is a foundational requirement for learning; and
16 (b) requiring families that are eligible for reduced-price school meals under the federal school
17 breakfast program and the national school lunch program to contribute to the cost of meals creates a barrier for
18 participation and a burden for school administrators for accounting and collection.
19 (2) From money appropriated for this purpose, the superintendent of public instruction shall
20 administer a program to distribute replacement funds to school districts electing to eliminate required reduced-
21 price copayments from reduced-price eligible pupils for school lunch and breakfast under a national or federal
22 program.
23 (3) If the amount of appropriated funds is insufficient for the program, the superintendent of public
24 instruction:
25 (a) may accept donations from private or out-of-state public sources to support the program; and
26 (b) shall request additional funding sufficient to support the program in the subsequent biennium.
27 (4) The superintendent of public instruction shall adopt rules necessary to administer the program.
28 (5) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
